### v3.0 — AI knowledge & logo
- Logo size increased: 54px, SECONDS text 2.15rem, nav-h 70px
- Logo has gold drop shadow glow
- DEFAULT_AI_KNOWLEDGE constant in accounts/models.py
- Pre-written generic watch shop FAQs auto-populate on first run
- AI strictly restricted: NEVER reveals sari-sari inventory to customers
- Store Settings AI tab: editable textarea pre-filled with default
- "Reset to Default" button restores the template
- get_ai_knowledge() method falls back to default if field is empty

## AI ASSISTANT RULES (built into system prompt)
1. Only answers watch, watch service, ordering, GCash, delivery, store info questions
2. NEVER reveals sari-sari inventory — stock, prices, availability
3. Responds in customer's language (Filipino or English)
4. Does not make up prices not in knowledge base
5. Suggests store contact if unsure

## DEFAULT AI KNOWLEDGE LOCATION
File: accounts/models.py
Constant: DEFAULT_AI_KNOWLEDGE
Auto-populates StoreSettings.ai_store_info on first run via get_settings()
Admin can edit in Store Settings → AI Assistant tab
Admin can reset to default via "Reset to Default" button

## SETUP (fresh install)
1. python -m venv venv
2. venv\Scripts\activate  (Windows) / source venv/bin/activate (Mac/Linux)
3. pip install -r requirements.txt
4. python manage.py migrate
5. python manage.py createsuperuser
6. python manage.py runserver
→ http://127.0.0.1:8000

## FIRST-RUN CHECKLIST
□ Login as superuser
□ Store Settings → Store Info: fill in store name, hours, address, Facebook URL
□ Store Settings → GCash & Delivery: fill in GCash number, name, fee, area
□ Store Settings → AI Assistant: fill in [price] placeholders with actual prices
□ Add watches in /watches/add/
□ Add sari-sari items in /inventory/add/
□ Post first announcement from dashboard

## UPDATE FORMAT
Minor  → SECONDS vers. 3.#  (e.g. 3.1, 3.2)
Major  → SECONDS vers. #.0  (e.g. 4.0)

### v3.1 — AI fix + logo on auth pages + FAQ update
- FIXED: AI assistant now works correctly using anthropic Python SDK
- FIXED: API key is stored in StoreSettings.anthropic_api_key (admin sets it in Store Settings → AI Assistant)
- FIXED: AI uses the actual FAQ from database — responses now reflect updates to knowledge base
- AI gives helpful error messages if key is missing or invalid instead of generic failure
- AI handles off-topic questions gracefully (tells user it can only help with store questions)
- ADDED: Anthropic API key field in Store Settings → AI Assistant tab (password input, never shown in plain text)
- CHANGED: Login, Register, Agreement, Logout pages now show animated SECONDS watch SVG logo instead of ⌚ emoji
- CHANGED: Logo is a reusable include at templates/includes/logo_svg.html (use anywhere with {% include 'includes/logo_svg.html' with size="64" %})
- UPDATED: DEFAULT_AI_KNOWLEDGE FAQ rewritten with:
  - Price ranges (₱130-340 battery, ₱140-200 straps, etc.) instead of [price] placeholders
  - Clear note that ALL prices are estimates varying by brand/model/condition
  - Wall clock repair note: varies by type (quartz, pendulum, chime, cuckoo, antique)
  - Layaway: No
  - Buy second-hand watches: Yes
  - Brands: depends on availability
  - Repair price FAQ answer improved
- ADDED: anthropic package to requirements.txt

## HOW TO SET UP THE AI ASSISTANT
1. Get a free API key from https://console.anthropic.com → API Keys
2. In SECONDS, go to Store Settings → AI Assistant tab
3. Paste your API key in the "Anthropic API Key" field
4. Click "Save AI Knowledge"
5. The AI chat button will now work for all users

### v3.3 — Gemini API key fix
- FIXED: Better error messages for Gemini API errors
- FIXED: "Host not in allowlist" error is now caught and gives admin clear instructions

## HOW TO FIX "Host not in allowlist" ERROR
This happens when your Gemini API key has Application Restrictions enabled.
Fix steps:
1. Go to https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
2. Find your API key and click the edit/pencil icon
3. Under "Application restrictions" — select "None"
4. Under "API restrictions" — select "Don't restrict key" (or ensure Generative Language API is allowed)
5. Click Save
6. Wait 1-2 minutes for the change to take effect
7. Test the AI chat again — it should work now

## HOW TO SET UP GEMINI API KEY (full steps)
1. Go to https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
2. Click "Create API Key"
3. Select a Google Cloud project (or create one — it's free)
4. Copy the key (starts with AIza...)
5. IMPORTANT: Click the edit icon on the key
6. Set Application restrictions to "None"
7. Set API restrictions to "Don't restrict key"
8. Save
9. In SECONDS: Store Settings > AI Assistant > paste the key > Save AI Knowledge
